The paper discusses improvements to Fully Convolutional Networks (FCN) for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a context network and dense skip connections, which are related to deep learning and neural networks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the segmentation datasets ADE20K, Pascal Context, Pascal VOC 2012, and SUN-RGBD, indicating that it falls under the sub-category of computer vision and machine learning for segmentation, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) possible sub-categories as well.
